==English==
=== Etymology ===
French '''mal'''&mdash;''ill'' + '''apropos'''&mdash;''purpose''.

''Also'' a reference to Mrs. Malaprop, a character in the play [[wikipedia|The Rivals]] by [[wikipedia|Richard Brinsley Sheridan]] (1775).  Throughout the play, Mrs. Malaprop uses inappropriate, but like-sounding, words for comic effect.

=== Noun ===
'''malapropism''' ([[malapropisms]])

# an absurdly inappropriate word that has been improperly used in place of a similar sounding word


==== Examples of malapropisms ====
* [[allegory]] => [[alligator]]
* [[pineapple]] => [[pinnacle]]
:* ''He's the pineapple of politeness.'' -- Sheridan, ''The Rivals''

